<w>wra<lb corresp="#b4"/><supplied>sañ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w>k<surplus>ä</surplus></w><w>tñi</w><w>tampeyaṃ</w>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣ<surplus>ä</surplus></w><w>kāsu</w>
<lb corresp="#b6"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>k<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... she (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to touch ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... memory ... near ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... fruit of ... they ... divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... without [any] other way. 1.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... towards the Buddha, the teacher ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... was proclaimed, honourable ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... receive the miserable beings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in your power ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... good ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">The right margin is preserved.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>(s)s oko</hi>: certainly <hi>oko</hi> is preceded by a genitive, e.g. <hi>pñintwiss</hi> 'of the merits'. The genitive ending is often geminated before <hi>oko</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>ceṣ ñäkciyā</hi>: <hi>ceṣ</hi> is nom.pl.m., while <hi>ñäkciyā</hi> is a pl.f., so probably obl.pl.f. <hi>ñäkciyā(s)</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>(ākṣi)ññu</hi>: alternatively, <hi>(okṣi)ññu</hi> or <hi>(kākñä)ññu</hi> are possible.</note></p>
         </div>
